lout
====

This module handles output for other scripts in this directory

	>>> import l, lout
	>>> lout.argv.test_args('-h ')
	Usage: try.py [options]
	<BLANKLINE>
	Options:
	  -q, --quiet   hide directories, blank lines, ...
	  -l, --lines   separate by returns (tabs is default)
	  -i, --ignore  Ignore files like those that subversion ignores
	  -h, --help    show this help message and exit

	>>> files = l.get_files()
	>>> files = l.remove_ignored(files)
	>>> names = l.get_names(files)
	>>> show( lout.format(names) )
